Package: hambridge
Architecture: arm64
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, adduser
Suggests: mosquitto
Description: Hardware-MQTT Bridge (evdev and VISCA over MQTT)
 HaMBridge (hambridge) is a headless Linux daemon that publishes Linux evdev input
 events to MQTT and, when configured, subscribes to MQTT device control topics and
 sends VISCA over serial (RS-232 / RS-485).
 .
 Configuration lives in /etc/hambridge/ (bridge.json, devices.json). The shipped
 systemd unit runs as user "hambridge"; create config and udev rules per the
 upstream packaging/ documentation.
